		<title> Worth OnLine - 93/09-Insider's Guide: Lyle Lovett's Houston</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6001.html?worth+PCFN18.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN18.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>93/09-Insider's Guide: Lyle Lovett's Houston</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						 
A newlywed's take on the best eat-in gas station, the swingingest bank, and the most relaxing rifle range<p>By Carla Koehl<p>Texas has bred some of the oddest people. But none is less likely than Lyle Lovett, the Houston native who thinks country music sounds better with a horn section. <p>At 35, Lovett has four albums under his 29-inch belt and a new one coming out next year. The summer concert tour he's just wrapped up to promote "Joshua Judges Ruth" ("my gospel/death album") was his biggest ever, and his mid-tour marriage to Julia Roberts bumped up his visibility a notch or two. He's also got a slightly twisted role in Robert Altman's upcoming Shortcuts, and he's still fending off agents who saw him in The Player. <p>If national attention has fazed him, it's impossible to tell. Lovett's still happily rooted in Texas, living on a piece of land that's been in his family since the 1840s. "Getting off the plane in the Houston heat, I don't mind that the back of my shirt is completely soaked through by the time I get to the car," he says. "I'm home."<p>Where To Stay: "One of my favorite hotels is the Wyndham Warwick [5701 Main Street]. When you look out the windows, oak trees are lining both sides of Main Street." <p>Favorite mexican restaurant: "Doneraki [2836 Fulton Street] is an old service station disguised as a restaurant. The tables are where the gas pumps used to be, and the restrooms are out around the outside of the building. They've got a mariachi band every night, and the best chicken fajitas and carne asada anywhere, plus menudo on weekends." <p>Where to buy a Western hat: "The Hat Store [5587 Richmond Avenue]. It's where my Dad bought his hats, and where I buy mine."<p>Favorite Nightspot: "My musical home is Anderson Fair Retail Restaurant [2007 Grant Street], the first place I ever played my own songs. Rockefeller's [3620 Washington Avenue] in the Heights neighborhood is also great. It used to be an old state bank, so of course the dressing room is in the vault." <p>Favorite All-Night Haunt: "Andy's Home Cafe [1115 East 11th Street]. They haven't got a liquor license, but they've got the best huevos rancheros at 2 a.m. It's the kind of place police go at night__which is great, because someone's car or tires or battery always seem to be getting stolen while you're inside. They make this warm mild salsa, and this green chile salsa that's so hot it'll bring tears to your eyes."<p>On a Free Afternoon: "Go to the Astrodome [Loop 610 at Kirby Drive], the eighth wonder of the world. They finished it in 1964, when I was a kid, and I remember it had one of the first fantastic scoreboards. It would light up like a fireworks display." <p>Where To Relax: "I hit Carter's Country gun range [6231 Treschwig Road]. I don't play golf, but shooting skeet with a 12- or 20-gauge seems to me the same kind of thing__concentrating so hard on one thing that your mind doesn't allow anything else in."<p> <p><p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
